         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Institution for Social and Policy Studies Records, Yale University, Records (RU 479). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_5f58e85f7c8aaf7bca24ea7f6f4a1ba8">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_27b1dcf7f4812f9770917c19c81d276e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Institution for Social and Policy Studies (ISPS) at Yale aims to facilitate interdisciplinary inquiry in the social sciences and public policy.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_45c22d553ece4ec0840f114b4f4a9b45">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of correspondence, student files, and administrative and subject files documenting the activities and operations of the Institution for Social and Policy Studies. Topics include fellowships, internships, evaluations and the City Program.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_91f80dc696984efb9048483792b6a10b">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
